column5: Was out fishing from the kayak on Saturday at Bronte. Only hooked one fish and never even knew I had it on the leadcore set-up until I decided to change lures. Although it looks a lot like a steelhead, I've ruled that out first because of the black mouth, triangular lower jaw and lack of spots below lateral line and on tail. I settled on a coho.      Anyone with some insight or is it too small to know, being roughly 7-8" long?
a lke ontario tough guy, clearly with something to prove to his fish buddies
Looks like a coho, sweet Kayak
Reminds me of a cutthroat trout, but i agree with pink salmon (ovalish spots), seeing how there aren't cutthroats in O.
google images for pink salmon smolt look very close to this... but? maybe rainbow trout? the big eyes are like a pink's
now, now!  MNR bio guy confirmed it a Coho....  what do they know anyhow? All I really care about is that I find a pile of its parents!
looks like a fish to me...
the lack of spots on the tail is a dead give away.
